rom a barrel to his fellow immigrants, who populated the tenement buildings of the Lower East Side. After graduating to a pushcart, then a horse-and-wagon, Joel Russ eventually made enough money to open a shop of his own. Russ &amp; Daughters was not its original name.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;"One of the first names was Russ's Cut Rate Appetizing," says Niki Russ Federman. "If there had been a son, it probably would have been Russ &amp; Sons." But Joel Russ had three daughters.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-87359" class="bucketwrap image x-large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 9504;         --source-height: 6336;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9504x6336+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F60%2F1a1e147149a3b419ffe75de9f6fb%2F20250826-russ-daughters-kc-16.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9504x6336+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F60%2F1a1e147149a3b419ffe75de9f6fb%2F20250826-russ-daughters-kc-16.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9504x6336+0+0/resize/1000/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F60%2F1a1e147149a3b419ffe75de9f6fb%2F20250826-russ-daughters-kc-16.jpg 1000w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9504x6336+0+0/resize/1300/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F60%2F1a1e147149a3b419ffe75de9f6fb%2F20250826-russ-daughters-kc-16.jpg 1300w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9504x6336+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F13%2F60%2F1a1e147149a3b419ffe75de9f6fb%2F20250826-russ-daughters-kc-16.jpg 1600w,